    {
      "unit_id": "p13_g03",
      "translation": "Despite measures to contain the spread of COVID-19 resulting in VONB declining to US$2.765 billion, sales momentum turned positive as movement restrictions eased, and we entered 2021 with very strong momentum, with VONB in the first two months growing 15% year-on-year. Our large and growing portfolio of in-force policies provided high-quality and recurring income streams, driving a 5% increase in OPAT in 2020, while UFSG generated during the period grew 7%. As at 31 December 2020, EV Equity reached a new high of US$67.2 billion, and the Group LCSM cover ratio stood at 374%, demonstrating our strong capital position and prudent financial management."
    }
  ]
}
